      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="6c5af998-357e-495e-b036-8a7538243e0c" type="Adjective">
          <Vi>buồn, đau buồn, u sầu</Vi>
          <En>feeling or showing sorrow; unhappy</En>
          <Example>She looked sad after hearing the bad news.</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="09fb207b-d72f-41b0-af7f-0567aac5193b">
              <Vi>Mô tả trạng thái cảm xúc khi gặp điều không vui, như mất mát, thất bại, hoặc tin xấu.</Vi>
              <En>Describes an emotional state when encountering unpleasant events, such as loss, failure, or bad news.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="6d6c21d1-9532-4815-8137-cca943d1c6bd">
              <Vi>Dùng để diễn tả vẻ mặt, hành vi thể hiện nỗi buồn (ví dụ: nhìn xuống, im lặng).</Vi>
              <En>Used to describe facial expressions or behaviors indicating sadness (e.g., looking down, being silent).</En>
            </Situation>
          </Situations>
        </Meaning>
